commit.message: Compatibility: Perl 5.16+ deprecates defined function on aggregates.
Copy edits for style, pointers and cruft.
Fix from user: typo glass in README

Remove superfluous prunedays in GetOptions (out long ago from subsequent behavior)
Update glastree.1: source and backup do _not_ need to be on the same fs for compression!
Outer dated dirs should be world readable; inner directories already govern security
Version bump for consistency; no new functionality
Dangit, forgot to update README version
Update version string; forgot in last dist!
Added NUL line separation to glastreeprune
Remove $target/$today check-fail, so multiple, same-day backups can happen
Modify install options for non-gnu platforms

Fix: GetOptions didn't include today/yesterday
Fix: Dot directories were being ignored
Fix: Symlinks to dirs were treated as dirs, not symlinks
We now search past 60 days for a prior directory, not just yesterday
Update to 0.54 with local directory target fix
